<section class="docs-section-card">
	<p class="docs-section-kicker">Usage rules</p>
	<h2>How the site should use these labels</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Use <code>implemented</code> when a reader can actually open the route or rely on the contract today.</li>
		<li>Use <code>partial</code> when the route exists but product maturity and data maturity are not the same thing.</li>
		<li>Use <code>experimental</code> when the surface is real but still unstable enough to avoid overpromising.</li>
		<li>Use <code>thesis</code> when the docs are describing direction, not current delivery.</li>
	</ul>
</section>

